is money, like

00:50:58.960 --> 00:51:00.340
most other things.

00:51:00.340 --> 00:51:02.880
Secondly, partnership.

00:51:02.880 --> 00:51:07.080
I'm particularly interested in
understanding how technology

00:51:07.080 --> 00:51:09.480
can make the world a better
place when you

00:51:09.480 --> 00:51:12.550
add into the trifecta--

00:51:12.550 --> 00:51:16.100
technology, make the world a
better place, and content.

00:51:16.100 --> 00:51:21.030
How do we technologically move
hearts and minds by placing

00:51:21.030 --> 00:51:26.070
content within the technology
that has that aspiration?

00:51:26.070 --> 00:51:29.840
And then, also, I believe that
measurement is something that

00:51:29.840 --> 00:51:32.710
a lot of people here
are very good at.

00:51:32.710 --> 00:51:35.950
And I think we're not
necessarily good at

00:51:35.950 --> 00:51:38.470
measurement yet.

00:51:38.470 --> 00:51:41.690
Psychologists measure all
sorts of human behavior.

00:51:41.690 --> 00:51:44.700
Not a lot of that has crossed
the street into the area of

00:51:44.700 --> 00:51:48.640
prosocial media to try to
understand whether we are

00:51:48.640 --> 00:51:50.800
being efficacious.

00:51:50.800 --> 00:51:55.160
A film like "The Blind Side--"
Sandy Bullock took a minuscule

00:51:55.160 --> 00:51:58.910
fee, took a year of her life,
and made that film.

00:51:58.910 --> 00:52:00.550
Did it to move the needle--

00:52:00.550 --> 00:52:02.490
I'm not saying it did
or it didn't--

00:52:02.490 --> 00:52:05.430
in race relations and in
understanding the challenges

00:52:05.430 --> 00:52:06.780
of kids in the inner city?

00:52:06.780 --> 00:52:08.440
What did it cost?

00:52:08.440 --> 00:52:09.990
And what was its value
to the world?

00:52:09.990 --> 00:52:11.310
And I don't mean
to pick on it.

00:52:11.310 --> 00:52:12.970
It was a fine film.

00:52:12.970 --> 00:52:14.810
I think we need to measure
this stuff.

00:52:14.810 --> 00:52:20.270
And another thing that may be
possible is the Venn diagram

00:52:20.270 --> 00:52:24.160
where technology and measurement
overlap.

